## Tier Summary

| Tier | Name | Key Components |
|------|------|----------------|
| 0 | External/Internet | Users (External, Internal, Mobile) |
| 1 | Perimeter/DMZ | Firewall/WAF, IIS Web Farm |
| 2 | Application | ExtranetWeb, SIS_INTRANET, Business/Data layers |
| 3 | Integration | WCF Services, PortalWebApi, REST APIs |
| 4 | Data | SQL Server (BD_EXTRANET, BD_INTRANET, BD_BI) |

## Communication Flows

| From | To | Protocol | Purpose |
|------|----|----------|---------|
| Users | WAF | HTTPS | Secure web access |
| WAF | IIS | HTTPS (terminated) | Load balanced requests |
| IIS | Web Apps | Local | Application hosting |
| Web -> Interfaces | Business Layer | In-process | Business logic |
| Business -> Data | SQL Server | T-SQL/SP | Data operations |
| Extranet | PortalWebApi | HTTP/HTTPS | Authentication |
| Both | WCF Services | SOAP/WCF | SAP/Agency integration |
| Intranet | API REST | HTTP/HTTPS | Complementary services |
| Both | Cross-DB | T-SQL | Shared master data |

## Security Concerns (from ADRs)

- **ADR-0003**: ConnectionStrings in Web.config without RSA encryption
- **ADR-0004**: BLOBs stored in database (VARBINARY) causing over-fetching
- Cookie-based authentication without complete hardening
- Missing declarative auth/CSRF protection
- Debug flag enabled in base config

## Missing Infrastructure

- Centralized logging
- Monitoring/APM
- Alerting system
- Backup/DR strategy
- CI/CD Pipeline
